**what is Dockerfile?**
A Dockerfile serves as a blueprint for creating Docker images. It contains a series of commands that Docker uses to assemble an image layer by layer. This automation ensures that applications run consistently across different environments, from development to production.

Example

FROM openjdk:17

WORKDIR /app

COPY target/banking-app.jar .

EXPOSE 8080

ENV ENVIRONMENT=prod

CMD ["java","-jar","banking-app.jar"]

